We create a sorted list **pairs_sum** of adjacent marble weights. We need it to calculate two sums of pair scores: **min_scores** - the smallest possible scores (pairs_sum[:-k + 1]) and **max_scores** - the largest possble scores (pairs_sum[k - 1:]). Then we calculate the difference between these scores and return it as an answer.

