# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
1. In the array, we get a composition of subarrays (bag-subarray) with only the head and tail elements and adjacent to each other.
2. In the result, both the head and tail elements of the whole array will be removed.
3. The rest of the selected element of the head and tail elements of the bags-subarrays are formed to the two-element subarrays, presenting the borders of the bags-subarray.
4. The border-subarrays can overlap with at most one elements.
5. The score can only be got from border-subarrays (border score)

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Initialize two PriorityQueues, one for the min values and the max ones
2. Iterate elements of `weights`
    1. For each index, sum the `i` one and `i + 1` one
    2. Collect the sum by both Min and Max PriorityQueues
3. Get the first `k - 1` elements of the PriorityQueues
4. Sum all the subtract result of the gotten max one and min one


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
  <!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
  - $$O(n * log(n))$$
  - $$n$$ for the iteration of each elements, $$log(n)$$ for processing of the PriorityQueues

- Space complexity:
  <!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
  - $$O(n)$$
  - Each PriorityQueue will store all of the elements of `weights`


# Code
```
function putMarbles(weights: number[], k: number): number {
    // In LeetCode 
    // the version of datastructures-js/priority-queue is 5.3.0

    // @ts-ignore
    const maxPq = new MaxPriorityQueue<number>();
    // @ts-ignore
    const minPq = new MinPriorityQueue<number>();

    for (let i = 0; i < weights.length - 1; i++) {
        const borderScore = weights[i] + weights[i + 1];
        maxPq.enqueue(borderScore);
        minPq.enqueue(borderScore);
    }

    let result = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < k - 1; i++) {
        const max = maxPq.dequeue().element;
        const min = minPq.dequeue().element;
        result += (max - min);
    }

    return result;
};
```

