# Intuition
- Put marbles to K bags is like starting from 1 bag and keep separating them until K. 
- Separating a bag is like creating a cutting point and the adjacent weights are added to the total weight.
- The first weight and last weigth will always be there, because they will be in bags.

# Approach
So just create an (n-1) length array containing the sum of 2 consecutive weights.
Max will be the sum of `K` biggest numbers
Min will be the sum of `K` smallest numbers

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n*logn)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$

# Code
```
func putMarbles(weights []int, k int) int64 {
    n := len(weights)

    if k == 1 {
        return int64(0)
    }


    max := 0
    min := 0

    think := make([]int, n-1)
    for i:=0; i<n-1; i++ {
        think[i] = weights[i]+weights[i+1]
    }

    sort.Ints(think)

    for i := 0; i<k-1; i++ {
        min += think[i] 
    }
    for i := n-2; i>n-1-k; i-- {
        max += think[i] 
    }

    return int64(max - min)
}
```

