# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Get all pairs added together. Use the original Vec, to save memory. Sort, and take the difference between the lowest and highest k.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
    O(n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

# Code
```
impl Solution {
    pub fn put_marbles(mut weights: Vec<i32>, k: i32) -> i64 {

        for i in 0..(weights.len() - 1) {
            weights[i] += weights[i+1];
        }
        weights.pop();

        weights.sort_unstable();

        let least: i64 = weights.iter().take((k-1) as _).map(|&x| x as i64).sum();
        let most: i64 = weights.iter().rev().take((k-1) as _).map(|&x| x as i64).sum();

        return most - least;
    }
}
```

